Title: Signal in the Fog (Opening)
Credit: Narrative Engine Full Film Mini Example
Author: Narrative Engine

EXT. OUTER HARBOR - NIGHT

Fog rolls low and metallic across black water. Emergency buoys blink, then vanish in white static.

A HOSPITAL SHIP HORN moans in the distance.

EXT. HARBOR WALL - CONTINUOUS

MARA VELEZ, 37, in an old weather jacket marked PORT SAFETY, studies a dead lighthouse line through binoculars.

Her radio crackles.

DISPATCH (V.O.)
Outer channel is blind. We have critical patients onboard and no visual lane.

Mara lowers the binoculars, jaw tight.

MARA
Patch me to Port Control. Priority red.

INT. PORT CONTROL LOBBY - MOMENTS LATER

Security doors remain locked. A suspended employee notice with Mara's name glows on a side monitor.

PORT DIRECTOR IAGO RELL appears on the intercom, calm and performative.

IAGO (V.O.)
Inspector Velez, you are not authorized in this facility.

MARA
A ship full of patients is drifting into a chemical wall.

(beat)
Authorize lighthouse relay now.

IAGO (V.O.)
Weather event protocols are active. Stand by for federal routing.

Mara looks back toward the fog where the horn sounds again, closer.

MARA
There is no federal route tonight.

She pulls an old brass key from her pocket and steps toward a maintenance door.

CUT TO:
